{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> βοάω</b>, <br /> <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>singular</i> βοάᾳ, <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>plural</i> βοόωσιν, <i>participle</i> βοόων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.394, 17.265, 15.687 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>Ionic dialect</i><i>imperfect</i> βοάασκε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 2.588 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]: <i>future</i> βοήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.48, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Doric dialect</i> βοάσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1154 (Lyric poetry); later βοήσω 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 3.792, “Anthologia Graeca” 7.32 (4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator), etc. (βοάσω 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1447 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] (Lyric poetry) is <i>aorist</i> <i>subjunctive</i>): <i>aorist</i> ἐβόησα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.15, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 772, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Epic dialect</i> βόησα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.847 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Doric dialect</i> βόασα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 16.14 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Ionic dialect</i> ἔβωσα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.337, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.146, 6th c.BC: Hipponax Iambographus 1, 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 3.23; sometimes in Comedy texts, 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 396, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 1155 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> βεβόηκα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Vitae Sophistarum” 2.1.11 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, βοώμενος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 1228 (perhaps _passive_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>aorist</i> βοήσατο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD(?): Quintus Smyrnaeus Epicus 10.465 \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>], <i>Ionic dialect</i> ἐβώσατο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 17.60 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; <i>participle</i> βοησάμενος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Antoninus Liberalis Mythographus 25.3 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>Ionic dialect</i> <i>aorist</i> ἐβώσθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.131 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> βεβόημαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 7.138 (from Aceratus)\">Refs</a>], <i>Ionic dialect</i> <i>participle</i> βεβωμένος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.39 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>pluperfect</i> ἐβεβόητο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 6.11.3 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<b>cry aloud, shout</b>, ὀξὺ βοήσας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.89; ὅσσον τε γέγωνε βοήσας 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 6.294; πᾶσα γὰρ πόλις βοᾷ 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1106 (Lyric poetry); ὡς δράκων β. [prev. author] “Th.” 381; β. γραμμάτων ἐν ξυλλαβαῖς [prev. work] 468 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; οἱ βοησόμενοι <b>men ready to shout</b> (in the ἐκκλησία), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 13.20 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ὁ δῆμος ἐβόησευ.., of acclamations, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 41.19 (3rd-4th c.AD),compare 2nd c.AD(?): Charito Scriptor Eroticus 1.1, +others, “IG” 12(9).906 (Chalcis, 3rd c.AD). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> of things, <b>roar, howl</b>, as the wind and waves, οὔτε.. κῦμα τόσον βοάᾳ ποτὶ χέρσον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.394 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>resound, echo</b>, ἀμφὶ δέ τ᾽ ἄκραι ἠϊόνες βοόωσιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 17.265; βοᾷ δὲ πόντιος κλύδων 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 431 (Lyric poetry), etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; βοᾷ δ᾽ ἐν ὠσὶ κέλαδος <b>rings</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Pers.” 605 \">Refs</a>]; τὸ πρᾶγμα φανερόν ἐστιν, αὐτὸ γὰρ βοᾷ it <b>proclaims</b> itself, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 921; φαίνεται αὐτὰ τὰ στοιχεῖα βοᾶν ὡς ἑλκόμενα 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 1091a10. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> with <i>accusative</i> <i>person</i>, <b>call to one, call on</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 6.36, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 205 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.92, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 7.2.5, 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 4.41:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] — <i>middle</i> βοησάμενοι δαίμονας Ant.Lib. [prev. cited] <br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i>, <b>call for, shout out for</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 772; β. τὴν βοήθειαν “Hellenica Oxyrhynchia” 10.2. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> <i>cognate</i>, β. βοάν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1153 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; β. μέλος, ἰωάν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 976, “Ph.” 216 (Lyric poetry); β. λοιγόν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 402 (Lyric poetry); ἄλγος 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 1310 (Lyric poetry): with double _accusative_, βοάσαθ᾽ ὑμέναιον ἀοιδαῖς ἰαχαῖς τε νύμφαν\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>sound aloud</b> the bridal hymn in honour of the bride, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 335 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs</a>]; ἔλεγον ἰήϊον ἐβόα κίθαρις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hyps. fragment” 3(1).iii 10. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <b>noise abroad, celebrate</b>, ἡ ῥάφανος ἣν ἐβοᾶτε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 15.7; πρήγματα βεβωμένα ἀνὰ Ἰωνίην 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.39; ἐβώσθησαν ἀνὰ τὴν Ἑλλάδα [prev. author] 6.131; οἱ βοηθέντες ἐπὶ χρήμασι 4th c.AD: Libanius Sophista “Orationes” 59.155 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; βεβοῆσθαι ἀπὸ τοῦ Μαραθῶνος, ἐκ τῶν ἀδικημάτων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Decl.” 11.18, 5.53. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>cry aloud</b> or <b>command in aloud noice</b> to do a thing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1287, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 297 (Lyric poetry); βοᾶν τινι ἄγειν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.8.12; ἐβόων ἀλλήλοις μὴ θεῖν [prev. work] 19 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also, <b>cry aloud</b> that.., Epicrat. 11.31 (<i>anapaest meter</i>); β. ὅτι.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.8.1, 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 125.5. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.6</b></Level3> <i>passive</i>, <b>to be filled with sound</b>, πᾶσαν δὲ χρὴ γαῖαν βοᾶσθαι ὑμνῳδίαις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Helena” 1434 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>to be deafened</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 1228. (Cf. βοή.) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0994","accentedUnicode":"βοάω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0310","matchingForm":"ἀναβοάω","stepTransliteration":"anaboaō","gloss":"to cry out","_zh_tw_Gloss":"喊著","_es_Gloss":"exclamar","_zh_Gloss":"喊着"},{"strongNumber":"G0995","matchingForm":"βοή","stepTransliteration":"boē","gloss":"outcry","_zh_tw_Gloss":"冤聲","_es_Gloss":"grito","_zh_Gloss":"冤声"}],"shortDef":"to call, cry out, shout","mediumDef":"to call, cry out, shout <br /><b>to cry out, call, shout; to exclaim, proclaim,</b> <ref='Mat.3.3; 15:34'>Mt. 3:3; 15:34</ref>; <ref='Act.8.7'>Acts 8:7;</ref> <greek>πρός τινα</greek>, <b>to invoke, implore the aid of any one,</b> <ref='Luk.18.7'>Lk. 18:7</ref>","stepGloss":"to cry out","stepTransliteration":"boaō","count":12,"_es_Definition":"llamar, clamar, gritar","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 呼叫, 吶喊<br>   1a) 充滿感情成分的; 喜樂的<br>   1b) 陳情或悲傷的呼喊<br>   1c) 嚴肅的宣告<br>3","_zh_Definition":"1) 呼叫, 呐喊<br> 1a) 充满感情成分的; 喜乐的<br> 1b) 陈情或悲伤的呼喊<br> 1c) 严肃的宣告<br>3","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"kêu lên ; kêu gào; kêu la ; gọi la (la lên, hét lên)","_zh_tw_Gloss":"喊著說, 呼喊","_es_Gloss":"clamar","_zh_Gloss":"喊着说, 呼喊"}]}